Its very obvious that your agency doesnt know what the FCRA is because from the looks of my credit report and all the errors i see you are disregarding it so heres my breakdown. 

1.The Fair Credit Reporting Act is the primary federal law that governs the collection and reporting of credit information about consumers. Its rules cover how a consumer 's credit information is obtained, how long it is kept, and how it is shared with othersincluding consumers themselves. 

2. What is a FCRA violation? 

Creditors give reporting agencies inaccurate financial information about you. Reporting agencies mixing up one person 's information with another 's because of similar ( or same ) last name or social security number. Agencies fail to follow guidelines for handling disputes. 

3. My rights under the fair credit reporting act Verify the accuracy of my report when it is required for employment purposes. 
Receive notification if information in my file has been used against me in applying for credit or other transactions. 
Disputeand have the bureaus correct and deleteinformation in my report that is incomplete, inaccurate, and unverifiable. 
Remove outdated, negative information ( after seven years in most cases, 10 in the case of bankruptcy ).

Product: Mortgage
Sub-issue: None
Consumer complaint narrative:
I requested PMI removal on my home, and was told that I could not given I have a second lien on my property ( in this case, a HELOC ). I was told that I would either be denied or I would have to shut down my HELOC. I am a mortgage loan originator myself, so I did some digging. It turns out, this is wrong and illegal. You can review the PMI removal requirements here : XXXX XXXX XXXXXXXX Nowhere does it mention subordinate liens being an issue. Additionally, it indicates that lenders may not add additional requirements on their end. I pointed all this out to Round Point Mortgage, and they initially pushed back. When I threatened to bring it to the CFPB, they acquiesced. So my personal issue is resolved, but here is the problem : they are enforcing this illegal policy against countless consumers, consumers who are not savvy enough to know better. The potential financial harm to consumers is huge. The FTC will take the case, but others need to make the same complaint. Others won't because they don't even know it is happening. CFPB seems to only take the case if you have an outstanding issue, and I don't have one anymore. But someone needs to address this, and I believe the CFPB is the most equipped organization to do so. 

I really hope the CFPB is able to correct this unjust policy. Thank you for your time on this matter.

I have received a response from Sears/Citibank in response to a complaint I made against this company. This response was also copied to you. Case # XXXX. Because this is Citibank, they were allowed to Police themselves and to send to me a condescending response in which they did Not address my complaint. My complaint had Nothing to do with discrimination of which they seemed to want to concentrate on. My complaint was in regard to the Promotional Interest free ( within 18 months ) purchase I made. When I called to set up the Promotional Payments, they agreed to the terms I asked for in order for me to pay this balance off by the expiration date. I knew I had to continue to make payments on my regular account balance, but they NEVER informed me they were going to add that purchase into my regular account. Since I made that purchase, they have deceptively raised the required payment on the existing balance I had, and have charged me a higher interest rate on that balance, as they stack an additional interest balance on the side, in an attempt to cause me to not be able to pay this promotion off, by the expiration date. I do not understand why these companies are allowed to treat consumers in this manner. I am asking that you inestigate this matter yourselves, or is their no protection for consumers after all. I do not have Citibank money, but I do have a Brain, and I do pay my debts. I think what they are being allowed to do is absolutely foul.

Dear Consumer Reporting Agency, I am writing to inform you that I recently received my credit report and found inaccurate information on it. I believe that this violates the Fair Credit Reporting Act ( FCRA ), particularly 15 USC 1681 and 15 USC 1681b.

REMOVE TRANSACTION HISTORY this is not a dispute, it is written instruction. please update immediately. if there is consumer debt for XXXX XXXX XXXX, please send 1099c, it is illegaly to charge off an account and report monthly payments XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXXXXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX The XXXX XXXX XXXX  XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX, TransUnion, XXXX XXXX Bank TransUnion, XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX  XXXX Mi TransUnion XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion XXXX XXXX XXXX TransUnion XXXX XXXX Furthermore, as a consumer, I demand that the utilization for the above accounts be updated to 5 % or below, or alternatively, that all utilization information be deleted due to inconsistencies across the board. I would appreciate a copy of my updated consumer report once the changes have been made. 

Please be aware that if you fail to respond satisfactorily and remove the negative account information, I may  take legal action against your company for FCRA violations, which includes civil liability and financial penalties. 

Please note that due to my current physical situation, which is the result of a prolonged COVID-19 sickness, I am unable to communicate by phone. Therefore, I request that we handle this matter electronically and through email. 

Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter.

Below is the summary of events : XXXX-Removed all funds from Account and called to have account closed. I was assured by the Bank of America representative that the account was closed and that I would be receiving an account closure confirmation letter within 10 business days. 
XXXX-Logged back into the Bank of America to determine and obtain any interest earned income statement for tax purposes. This is when I FIRST noticed that the checking account was still active and had a negative balance of - {$6.00}. There were deposits since my initial call from my previous employer of {$19.00} ( approx. XX/XX/XXXX ) and {$34.00} ( approx. XX/XX/XXXX ) totaling {$53.00}. The Bank charged me low balance maintenance fees for XXXX, XXXX, XXXX, XXXX, and XX/XX/XXXX ; {$12.00} each month totaling {$60.00}.

However, the representatives I spoke with repeatedly instructed me to pay the Bank the negative - {$6.00} the Bank negligently caused so that I can be allowed to close the account. I refused and asked to zero out the balance and close my account. Again, they suggested it would be closed and that I would receive a confirmation letter shortly. 
XXXX-Logged into account once again and saw that the account was not closed and the negative balance increased by {$12.00} ( additional maintenance charge added for XX/XX/XXXX ) to - {$18.00}. I spoke to representative " XXXX '' from Nevada ; employee # XXXX. I explained again the situation and her supervisor ; Senior Client Advocate ( who I did not speak to ) named XXXX refunded the account 2 months worth of maintenance fees ( {$24.00} ) to bring my account positive to {$5.00}. Again, they said it would be closed, I would receive a confirmation letter and the remaining balance on the account would be sent via postal mail. 
XX/XX/XXXX ( today ) -Logged into account again and saw the account was still active and spoke to XXXX from Deposit Department in Arkansas . I explained the situation once again and asked her if I would be billed a maintenance fee since the account was not closed earlier in the month and she could not answer this basic question. Her supervisor from the Consumer Deposit Dept, named XXXX ; employee # XXXX again assured me the account would be closed, I would receive a confirmation letter, the remaining funds in the account would be sent to me via postal mail and I will not receive another maintenance charge. Consumer complaint narrative: I have a CLOSED visa credit account at TD Bank NA which is disputed and affected by a natural or declared natural disaster. The FCRA and XXXX XXXX protocols require reporting my CLOSED account as ( 1 ) disputed and ( 2 ) affected by natural or declared disaster. However, my XXXX, XXXX and XXXX credit reports fail to accurately reflect that my account is disputed AND affected by a natural or declared disaster. Therefore, my credit reports are inaccurate and not complete for failure to contain the mandatory information. Either delete my TD Bank NA visa account or include the statutory reference that my account is both disputed by consumer AND affected by a natural or declared disaster. I insist on 100 % compliance with the FCRA and all XXXX XXXX protocols including the reporting on paper credit reports of all data reported in the XXXX XXXX submissions. I also insist on 100 % compliance with necessary internal controls to prevent Facially False Data from appearing on my credit reports. My credit report has daily entries where the data entry for Closed account is removed then at some time later replaced with a dispute code then deleted again with a code for consumer affected by a natural disaster thereby affectively changing a closed account to an Open account. Since the entire XXXX XXXX system is incapable of complying with the FCRA to prevent Facially False Data from reappearing ( such as a dead person coming back to life ) ( or a closed account being later reported as open ) then my account must be permanently deleted to avoid further willful violations of the FCRA.

Consumer complaint narrative:
Fifth Third Bank on XX/XX/XXXX put my bank account into closure for " risk mitigation ''. At this moment in time I was running a campaign across the country in XXXX XXXX California. 
I was able to take money out the ATM through a tedious process until XX/XX/XXXX, they lied and said my bank card was deactivated and I could no longer take money out the ATM. 

Their decision to do this forced me to not be able to continue running my campaign and paying my contractors. 

This also forced me and my team into homelessness because we had no access to money unless we went into a fifth Third Bank which is nowhere close to XXXX XXXX CA. 

On XX/XX/XXXX fifth third bank sent a cashier 's check to my home in north Carolina that was the final amount in my account. 

I borrowed money from my family in order to make it back home. 

On XX/XX/XXXX I took the check to a fifth third bank in XXXX north Carolina and they refused to cash it, even though it was a fifth third cashier 's check. They told me I could sign it over to my aunt and they would allow it to be cashed, then the teller at the branch refused to cash it. 

We then took the check to the local credit union to cash, in my aunt 's account because I had already signed it over to her, which fifth third bank refused to honor because I did not verify who I was before the check could get verified and put my aunt 's account into negative {$2500.00} I then continued my mobile deposit on XX/XX/XXXX with XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX and while on the phone with them verified myself and the check and fifth third bank honored the check. 

Then on XX/XX/XXXX, that following Friday fifth third sent an email to XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX to not honor the check which put my account in the negative {$1600.00}.

Consumer complaint narrative:
On XX/XX/2023 I mailed a letter to Experian demanding proper verification of their claimed debt that they have furnished on my credit report. Per certified mail receipt, they received this letter on XX/XX/2023. 

Experian has responded to me by citing Section 605B ( c ) ( 1 ) and Section 611 ( a ) ( 3 ) ( A ) of the Fair Credit Reporting Act in an attempt to hide the fact that they have not responded properly to my demand that they fulfill their legal obligation. They are attempting to claim that this alleged debt is verified without having ever done any verification. They attempt to say that it is on the creditor to correct the information, but Experian is the one furnishing this information PUBLICLY and harming MY reputation. Which makes them LIABLE and obligated to legally validate their claims.

In the letter I demanded that they send me a sworn proof of verification affidavit to show how Experian is legally claiming that the account XXXX XXXX is in fact accurate, valid, and complete ( per 15 USC 1681e ( e ) ( 1 ) ).

Because I have never received from Experian any sworn statements, affidavit of truth with notary signature, or any statements under oath - there has been no verification made under U.S. Federal Law.

I have also demanded that they have a party identified by position and authority at Experian who has first-hand-knowledge of this matter swearing that I explicitly gave Experian written instruction to furnish the XXXX  account on my consumer credit report. I demanded that they state this under oath, with their wet ink signature and have a notary present, on the previously mentioned Proof of Verification Affidavit ( Pursuant to 15 U.S.C. 1681b ).

I also informed them that I require to witness the original wet-ink contract that I allegedly signed which created the alleged debt which Experian is furnishing on my credit report. ( Failure to produce the original contract agreement will be evidence of fraud in the claim that I owe any debt and that Experian is allowed by law to report on my credit report. ( Pursuant to UCC 3-302 ) ) I am only attempting to have the records corrected to what they rightfully should be legally and lawfully. Each phone call, online interaction, and mail piece are being documented for this purpose.

It would be advisable that Experian assure the records they are furnishing publicly on my consumer credit report are in order before I am forced to take legal action. ( Pursuant to 15 U.S. Code 1681n )

Consumer complaint narrative: XXXX XXXX, 2022 I called Bridgecrest to inform them that I had an emergency and would not be able to make the payment for that month. I asked if the payment could be applied to the end of the loan. I was informed that I'd need to cancel my auto pay and allow myself to become " past due '' and to call back. I called back after allowing my payment due date to pass, and was told there was nothing they'd do other than note the account and that I needed to make the next payment. My pay day came around, and I made the payment on XX/XX/XXXX however, it still will have me one month behind. I call again and ask if the payment can be deferred. I'm then told that extensions are approved on a case by case basis, and that I should not have made my payment. I was then told to yet again, call back later this month and ask again. I mentioned I'd complain to the CFPB because there has to be another remedy other than having the customer call each month. They then tell me they can offer a payment plan that would not get me caught up until XXXX, and would still accrue interest. I was transferred to a manager that reiterated that the only thing I could do was continue to call each month and ask, and it is up to them to decide if they will allow it.

Consumer complaint narrative: Representatives of BoA visited my business and offered a new product service for small business owners. I made sure this was a BoA product and it was confirmed that it was " Merchant Services, '' so I signed up. All seemed to be well for a period of time. I later noted a debit of {$10000.00} and a subsequent debit of {$3500.00}. When a large charge reaches my account I am always contacted by the bank 's Fraud Department to confirm the legitimacy of the charge. That did not occur with these transactions. Thereafter, I took notice of a number of chargebacks ( refunds ) in the account under the same institution. All of the transactions have since totaled around {$20000.00}. I called Bank of America for assistance because I was completely confused but I was told I would need to visit my local branch. Throughout several weeks I spoke with a number of people who explained to me that Bank of America discontinued it's relationship with that merchant, but did not notify any account holders. This service was again presented by, from, and as a Bank of America product. Due to this lack of communication and transparency I incurred charges and chargebacks from the company once their agreement ceased. Bank of America refused to help me dispute the charges and the reversal payments which occured as a result of them ending their contract with the service company. I explained thoroughly that only after the charges had I been told this was a partnership and they were ending their relationship. If I were made aware I would have taken the steps to do the same. Bank of America presented the service directly to me but did not any way shape or form let me know this product/service would no longer be offered. This situation is beyond unsettling because they refuse to move a toe in trying to assist me in protecting my account, disputing the charges, or getting my money returned back to me. They simply apologized and stated there is nothing they can do. They have completely thrown their hands up and not taken responsibility, not tried to help me in any way, nor explain how nor why I wasn't kept informed about anything. These are the those I continuously pleaded for help from XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX
